feed.title: Terrestrial Energy Inc. to Begin Trading on Nasdaq under Ticker Symbol “IMSR” on October 29, 2025 After Successful Business Combination with HCM II Acquisition Corp. | IMSRW Stock News
feed.summary: Terrestrial Energy Inc. will commence trading on Nasdaq under the ticker symbol "IMSR" on October 29, 2025, following its successful business combination with HCM II Acquisition Corp. This merger secured over $292 million in gross proceeds to accelerate the deployment of Terrestrial Energy's Integral Molten Salt Reactor (IMSR) nuclear technology. The IMSR aims to provide clean, low-cost industrial heat and electricity, addressing global energy demands with strategic partnerships and government program selections.

feed.title: HCM II Acquisition Corp. SEC 10-Q Report
feed.summary: HCM II Acquisition Corp. (SPAC) has filed its Form 10-Q for Q2 2025, detailing financial performance including $1.29 million net income. The company is also pursuing PIPE financing and must complete the business combination by August 19, 2026, to avoid liquidation.

feed.title: Terrestrial Energy Inc. Completes Business Combination with HCM II Acquisition Corp.
feed.summary: Terrestrial Energy Inc. has completed its business combination with HCM II Acquisition Corp., raising over $292 million in gross proceeds to accelerate the deployment of its Integral Molten Salt Reactor (IMSR) nuclear technology. The combined company will begin trading on Nasdaq under the ticker symbol "IMSR" on October 29, 2025. This merger provides significant capital and support for Terrestrial Energy's growth plans, positioning it to meet the rising demand for clean, reliable nuclear energy.

feed.title: Nuclear Innovation: Terrestrial Energy's $280M SPAC Deal Brings Next-Gen Reactor Tech to Nasdaq
feed.summary: HCM II Acquisition Corp. (NASDAQ: HOND) and Terrestrial Energy have filed a draft S-4 registration statement with the SEC for their $280 million SPAC merger. The deal will create a publicly traded company on Nasdaq under the ticker "IMSR," focusing on advanced Generation IV Integral Molten Salt Reactor (IMSR) technology for small modular nuclear plants. The transaction, which includes $50 million in PIPE commitments, is anticipated to close in Q3 or Q4 2025, subject to stockholder approval.

feed.title: HCM II Acquisition Corp. and Terrestrial Energy Announce
feed.summary: HCM II Acquisition Corp. (Nasdaq: HOND) and Terrestrial Energy Inc. have filed a draft registration statement on Form S-4 with the SEC for their proposed business combination. The transaction, expected to close in Q3 or Q4 2025, will provide approximately $280 million in gross proceeds to accelerate the commercial deployment of Terrestrial Energy’s proprietary Generation IV Integral Molten Salt Reactor (IMSR) technology. This filing includes a preliminary proxy statement/prospectus, offering details about both companies and the merger that will see the combined entity listed on Nasdaq under the ticker symbol "IMSR."

feed.title: HCM II Acquisition Corp. and Terrestrial Energy Inc. File Draft Registration Statement for Proposed Business Combination
feed.summary: HCM II Acquisition Corp. and Terrestrial Energy Inc. have filed a draft registration statement with the SEC for their proposed business combination, aiming to list the combined company, focused on small modular nuclear plants, on Nasdaq under the ticker "IMSR". This transaction is expected to generate approximately $280 million in gross proceeds to accelerate the deployment of Terrestrial Energy's Integral Molten Salt Reactor technology.
